62 (B) In the event the committee adopts a report that does not include suggestions for
63 proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file the report, subject to subparagraph (C)
64 of this paragraph.
65 (C) No report shall be filed unless the same has been approved prior to the date of
66 abolishment specified in this resolution by majority vote of a quorum of the committee.
67 A report so approved shall be signed by the chairperson of the committee and filed with
68 the Clerk of the House of Representatives.
69 (D) In the absence of an approved report, the chairperson may file with the Clerk of the
70 House of Representatives a copy of the minutes of the meetings of the committee in lieu
71 thereof.
72 (7) Abolishment. The committee shall stand abolished on December 1, 2025.
73 SECTION 2.
74 Creating the House Study Committee on the Affordability and Accessibility of Georgia's
75 Legitimation Process; and for other purposes.
76 WHEREAS, in Georgia, a biological father who is not married to the mother of his child at
77 the time of such child's birth must file a separate legal petition in order to legitimate the child
78 and obtain legal rights as a parent; and
79 WHEREAS, the benefit of having two parents responsible for a child is known to have a
80 positive effect on a child's welfare; and
81 WHEREAS, in Georgia, biological fathers who wish to obtain parental rights to their
82 children are discouraged from doing so, often due to a lack of resources or awareness of the
83 costs associated with legitimation; and
- 4 -

