84 WHEREAS, it is worth considering whether the legitimation process in Georgia may be
85 improved in a way that yields it more affordable and accessible, particularly for those
86 biological fathers with limited financial resources.
87 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES:
88 (1) Creation of House study committee. There is created the House Study Committee
89 on the Affordability and Accessibility of Georgia's Legitimation Process.
90 (2) Members and officers. The committee shall be composed of five members of the
91 House of Representatives. The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall designate
92 a member of the committee as chairperson of the committee.
93 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
94 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
95 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
96 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
97 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
98 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
99 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
100 (5) Allowances and funding. The legislative members of the committee shall receive
101 the allowances provided for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia
102 Annotated. The allowances authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any
103 member of the committee for more than three days unless additional days are authorized.
104 Funds necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
105 appropriated to the House of Representatives.
106 (6) Report.
107 (A) In the event the committee adopts any specific findings or recommendations that
108 include suggestions for proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file a report of the
