153 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES:
154 (1) Creation of House study committee. There is created the House Study Committee
155 on Gaming in the State of Georgia.
156 (2) Members and officers. The committee shall be composed of seven members. The
157 members of the committee shall be the chairpersons of the House Committee on Ways
158 and Means, the House Committee on Regulated Industries, and the House Committee on
159 Economic Development and four other members of the House of Representatives
160 appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives, one of whom shall be
161 designated by the Speaker of the House of Representatives to serve as chairperson of the
162 committee.
163 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
164 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
165 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
166 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
167 shall hold at least four public hearings at various locations throughout this state and at
168 least one meeting to discuss and finalize findings. Such hearings and meeting shall be
169 conducted at such places and at such times as deemed necessary or convenient to enable
170 the committee to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
171 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
172 (5) Allowances and funding.
173 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
174 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
175 (B) The allowances authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any member
176 of the committee for more than three days unless additional days are authorized. Funds
177 necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
178 appropriated to the House of Representatives.
- 8 -

